{{Infobox Politician | image = Riksmarskalken Svante Lindqvist med hustrun Catharina.jpg |honorific-prefix = [[Excellency|His Excellency]] | name = Svante Lindqvist | caption = Svante Lindqvist with wife Catharina prior to the [[wedding of Princess Madeleine of Sweden and Christopher O'Neill]] on 8 June 2013. | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1948|4|26|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Stockholm]], [[Stockholm County]] | residence = | office = [[Marshal of the Realm (Sweden)|Marshal of the Realm of Sweden]] | monarch = [[Carl XVI Gustaf]] | term_start = 1 January 2010 | term_end = 30 August 2018 | predecessor = [[Ingemar Eliasson]] | successor = [[Fredrik Wersäll]] | party = | religion = | occupation = | majority = | relations = | spouse = Catharina Lindqvist | alma_mater = [[Royal Institute of Technology]] | children = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Lars Svante Albert Lindqvist''' (born 26 April 1948) is a [[Swedish people|Swedish]] [[History of technology|historian]] who has been the [[Marshal of the Realm (Sweden)|Marshal of the Realm of Sweden]] and chief of the [[Royal Court of Sweden]] from 1 January 2010 until 30 August 2018.<ref>[http://www.kungahuset.se/ovrigt/pressrum/pressmeddelanden/aretsarkiv/professorsvantelindqvistnyriksmarskalk.5.4d52a9051226f69aa7780006183.html Press release from the Royal Court on August 26, 2009: Professor Svante Lindqvist new Marshal of the Realm]</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.svd.se/hovet-far-ny-riksmarskalk|title=Hovet får ny riksmarskalk {{!}} SvD|last=TT|work=SvD.se|access-date=2018-10-17|language=sv}}</ref>
== Biography == Lindqvist is the son of [[architect]] Åke E. Lindqvist and Barbro Åström. He holds an [[Master of Science in Engineering|MSE]] in [[engineering physics]] from the [[Royal Institute of Technology]] since 1977. After contact with [[Torsten Althin]], he had written a thesis with focus on historical technology.<ref>[http://www.lib.chalmers.se/librarypremises/exhib/utmar08a1.pdf Chalmers: Torsten Althin (1897–1982)]{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He holds a [[Ph.D]] in science and ideas history from [[Uppsala University]] since 1984.<ref name="SL webb">[http://www.svantelindqvist.com/ Svante Lindqvists webbplats], read on 14 July 2009</ref> His [[doctoral dissertation]] was about the introduction of the [[steam engine]] in Sweden in the early 18th century.
Lindqvist later became a professor of art history at the Royal Institute of Technology, but left in 1998 to become head of the [[Nobel Museum]], which was inaugurated in 2001.
Lindqvist is a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Engineering Sciences]] since 1992, the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]] (KVA) since 1994 and the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Letters, History and Antiquities]] since 2002.
On 1 July 2009 he was appointed the KVA's [[praeses]], for a three-year term.<ref>[http://kva.se/sv/pressrum/pressmeddelanden-2008-2001/Svante-Lindqvist-blir-ny-preses-vid-Kungl-Vetenskapsakademien/ Royal Academy of Sciences - Svante Lindqvist is the new praeses at the Royal Academy of Sciences, Press Release on 18 December 2008.]</ref> He was succeeded by [[Barbara Cannon]] on 1 July 2012.<ref>[http://kva.se/sv/pressrum/Pressmeddelanden-2012/Barbara-Cannon-blir-Kungl-Vetenskapsakademiens-nya-preses/ Royal Academy of Sciences - Barbara Cannonis the new praeses at the Royal Academy of Sciences], Press Release on 7 February 2012.</ref>
== Distinctions == *{{flagicon|Sweden}} [[H. M. The King's Medal]] of the 12th size in the [[Order of the Seraphim]] ribbon (Kong: sGM12mserafb) "for significant contributions in the museum sector and in the subject of technology history," on 28 January 2010. *{{flagicon|Estonia}} Member 1st Class of [[Order of the Cross of Terra Mariana]] (EPTMk1kl) in connection with the Estonian state visit on 18 January 2011.
