'''Tripp Trapp''' is an adjustable wooden [[high chair]] for children. It was developed by the [[Norway|Norwegian]] furniture designer [[Peter Opsvik]] for the company [[Stokke AS]].<ref name="Bruce 2002">{{cite book | title=Design in Business| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yU7U9JG8wUcC&pg=PT37&dq=tripp+trapp+stokke&lr=&client=firefox-a| last=Bruce| first=Margaret |author2=J. R. Bessant | year=2002| page=30| publisher=Financial Times / Prentice Hall| isbn=0273643746}}</ref><ref name="Crainer 2004">{{cite book | title=Financial Times Handbook of Management: The State of the Art| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R7fMHYTCJdQC&pg=PA272&dq=tripp+trapp+stokke&client=firefox-a| last=Crainer| first=Stuart|author-link1=Stuart Crainer| author2=Des Dearlove | author-link2=Des Dearlove|year=2004| page=272| publisher=Financial Times / Prentice Hall| isbn=0273675842}}</ref> Launched in 1972, over time it became a best-selling item.<ref name="scandes">{{cite book |title=Scandinavian Design | last=Fiell |first=Charlotte J.| last2=Fiell |first2=Peter |publisher=Taschen |year=2002 |isbn=978-3822858820 |pages=490–491}}</ref> Peter Opsvik is also the designer, in cooperation with Hans Christian Mengshoel, of the original ''Balans'' [[kneeling chair]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.violetofficesupplies.co.uk/product-category/accommodation-furniture/office-furniture/kneeling-chair-office-furniture/|title=Used Kneeling chair and it’s Vital Role in your Life|last=|first=|date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-31}}</ref><ref name="scandes" />

== Development history ==
[[Peter Opsvik]] noticed that his son Tor had no chair that could position him at the correct height at the family dinner table and enable him to participate with the rest of the family. He then developed a chair that was adjustable and changed with the size of his son as he grew bigger.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stokke.com/no-no/highchair/tripp-trapp-product-concept.aspx |accessdate=May 21, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130601003406/http://www.stokke.com/no-no/highchair/tripp-trapp-product-concept.aspx |archivedate=June 1, 2013 }}</ref>

Tripp Trapp did not sell well in the beginning, but a news segment on Norwegian television in 1974 sparked an interest that has gained strength over the years. By 2016 Tripp Trapp had sold more than 10 million chairs<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stokke.com/global/stokke-stories/stokke-stories-product-news/tripp-trapp-anniversary-collection-2016.html|title=Celebrating 10 million Tripp Trapp® chairs since 1972|website=USA|language=en-US|access-date=2017-06-08}}</ref>.

== Product characteristics ==

Tripp Trapp has a seat and footrest that can be adjusted in both height and depth. Thus the chair can be adapted as the child  grows. Additionally the chair is correctly spaced and so stable that even a young toddler can climb up into the chair safely by themselves. The Tripp Trapp high chair is made from [[beechwood]] with some limited editions in oak.

